MESSAGES of congratulations are rolling in for award-winning gospel artist Jumbo Nyangiwe, who’s bought himself a car. Jumbo announced the news on Facebook. He wrote: “God is good. Congratulations. Sibongukwanda.” Gospel artist Thinah Zungu revealed the car was bought cash. He said: “My friend has just bought a car cash from selling his music. Congratulations, Somju.” Both announcements were accompanied by a photo of Jumbo standing in front of a Mercedes-Benz holding the keys. Jumbo’s colleagues, friends and fans have been flooding him with congratulatory messages since Tuesday, 8 February.\ ALSO READ : OWEN BAGS R2M FOR NEW VENTURE Gospel artist Mxolisi “Ollie Mkhize posted: “You deserve it my brother, you’ve worked so hard, congratulations.” Meloh Wam Jele commented: “That’s awesome! Congratulations! In no time he’ll be building a double- storey house and a swimming pool. Siyakubongela, soMju.” Nokulunga Fakazile Dhlomo said: “Congratulations to Jumbo, grace upon grace. I’m a big fan.” The singer was formally introduced on the gospel scene in December 2016 as one of the artists who sang at Sfiso Ncwane’s memorial service. He rose to fame the next year when he won the Best Song of the Year at the 10th Crown Gospel Awards for his song, Singenise. He’s never looked back since then as he continued to win awards. This year he was eyeing the song of the year title, but lost to DJ Hlo. 